{
  "texts": [
    "Their Recursive Autonomy Identification (RAI) algorithm assumes discrete variables and faithfulness, and starts with a complete undirected graph.",
    "Like the PC algorithm, RAI uses CI tests of increasing order.",
    "However, edge orientation is undertaken after edge removal at each conditioning set size, and this can allow RAI to identify autonomous subgraphs.",
    "These can be learnt independently of each other through recursive calls of the algorithm.",
    "Figure 10, based on the example given in their paper, illustrates these concepts."
  ]
}